## 2. Diagramme de Classes (Modèle de Données Complet)

Ce diagramme représente la totalité des collections Dexie/IndexedDB, basées sur les types de `types.ts`.

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class User {
        +String id
        +String email
        +String name
        +String firstName
        +String phone
        +String nationality
        +Integer age
        +String photo
        +Role role
        +String organizationId
        +String serviceId
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class Organization {
        +String id
        +String name
        +String type
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class Service {
        +String id
        +String organizationId
        +String name
        +String arrondissement
        +Location location
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class Incident {
        +String id
        +IncidentType type
        +PersonAge personAge
        +IncidentStatus status
        +String title
        +String description
        +Location location
        +List~String~ photos
        +String reportedBy
        +String assignedServiceId
        +String assignedTo
        +Date createdAt
        +Date updatedAt
    }

    class Observation {
        +String id
        +String type
        +String incidentId
        +String description
        +Location location
        +List~String~ photos
        +String reportedBy
        +Float aiSimilarityScore
        +String status
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class TimelineEvent {
        +String id
        +String incidentId
        +String actionType
        +String description
        +String visibility
        +String createdBy
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class Watcher {
        +String userId
        +List~String~ arrondissements
        +List~String~ favoriteQuartiers
        +Boolean active
    }

    class Alert {
        +String id
        +String title
        +String message
        +String level
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class NewsPost {
        +String id
        +String type
        +String title
        +String content
        +String authorId
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class Rumor {
        +String id
        +String submittedBy
        +String content
        +String photo
        +String status
        +String officialResponse
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class SOSAlert {
        +String id
        +String userId
        +Location location
        +String status
        +Date resolvedAt
        +Date createdAt
    }

    class Location {
        +Float lat
        +Float lng
        +String address
        +String arrondissement
        +String quartier
    }

    %% Relations
    User "1" -- "0..1" Watcher : peut être
    User "1" -- "*" Incident : signale / enquête sur
    User "1" -- "*" Observation : soumet
    User "1" -- "*" Rumor : soumet
    User "1" -- "*" SOSAlert : déclenche
    
    Organization "1" *-- "*" Service : possède
    Service "1" o-- "*" User : emploie (Agents/Superviseurs)
    Service "1" -- "*" Incident : gère
    
    Incident "1" *-- "*" TimelineEvent : contient
    Incident "1" o-- "*" Observation : lie
```
